1. DEFINITIONS

"Consumer Attorney" means any natural person who is a licensed attorney, and any
law firm, legal organization, or legal aid entity with which such attorney is
associated, where the attorney and anyone associated with his or her firm
primarily represent plaintiffs and do not defend on an ongoing basis any
insurance company(ies), manufacturer(s), governmental entity(ies), common
carrier(s), corporation(s), public utility(ies), or other organization in
personal injury, wrongful death, workers' compensation, employment, or other
consumer-related litigation.

"Defense Practitioner" means any natural person, law firm, legal organization,
corporate legal department, insurance company, third-party administrator, or any
other entity that does not meet the definition of Consumer Attorney set forth
above. Without limitation, this includes any person or entity that defends, on
an ongoing basis, any insurance company(ies), manufacturer(s), governmental
entity(ies), common carrier(s), corporation(s), public utility(ies), or other
organization in personal injury, wrongful death, workers' compensation,
employment, or other consumer-related litigation.

"Non-Commercial Use" means use of the Software solely for personal, educational,
academic, research, or charitable purposes that do not involve, directly or
indirectly, the generation of revenue, commercial advantage, or monetary
compensation. Non-Commercial Use expressly includes use by law school clinics,
legal aid organizations, and pro bono programs regardless of the user's status
as a Consumer Attorney or Defense Practitioner.

"You" or "Your" means the individual or entity exercising rights under this
License.

"Licensor" means the copyright holder(s) or entity authorized by the copyright
holder(s) to grant rights under this License.

"Modification" or "Derivative Work" means any work based upon the Software,
including but not limited to any revision, enhancement, adaptation, translation,
abridgment, condensation, expansion, or any other form in which the Software may
be recast, transformed, or adapted.

"Distribute" or "Distribution" means to make available to third parties by any
means, including but not limited to publishing, deploying, sublicensing,
selling, or otherwise transferring copies of the Software or Derivative Works.

"Written License Agreement" means a separate written agreement, executed by the
Licensor and the Defense Practitioner, setting forth the specific terms,
conditions, fees (if any), and limitations under which the Defense Practitioner
may use the Software.


2. GRANT OF RIGHTS TO CONSUMER ATTORNEYS

Subject to the terms and conditions of this License, the Licensor hereby grants
to any Consumer Attorney a perpetual, worldwide, non-exclusive, royalty-free,
irrevocable license to:

    (a) Use, copy, and run the Software for any purpose, including commercial
        use in the Consumer Attorney's law practice;

    (b) Modify the Software and create Derivative Works;

    (c) Distribute copies of the Software or Derivative Works to other Consumer
        Attorneys, provided that such Distribution includes a complete copy of
        this License and all copyright and attribution notices;

    (d) Merge the Software with other software and use the resulting combined
        work, provided that the portions of such combined work that constitute
        the Software or Derivative Works thereof remain subject to this License;
        and

    (e) Sublicense the rights granted herein to other Consumer Attorneys,
        subject to the same terms and conditions of this License.


3. GRANT OF RIGHTS FOR NON-COMMERCIAL USE

Subject to the terms and conditions of this License, the Licensor hereby grants
to any person or entity a perpetual, worldwide, non-exclusive, royalty-free
license to use, copy, modify, and distribute the Software solely for
Non-Commercial Use, provided that:

    (a) All copies and Derivative Works include a complete copy of this License
        and all copyright and attribution notices;

    (b) The Software and any Derivative Works are not used, directly or
        indirectly, in connection with the defense of any insurance company,
        manufacturer, governmental entity, common carrier, corporation, public
        utility, or other organization in personal injury, wrongful death,
        workers' compensation, employment, or other consumer-related litigation;
        and

    (c) Any Distribution of the Software or Derivative Works for Non-Commercial
        Use prominently states that such use is limited to Non-Commercial
        purposes under this License.


4. RESTRICTIONS ON DEFENSE PRACTITIONERS

No Defense Practitioner may use, copy, modify, distribute, sublicense, or
otherwise exercise any rights with respect to the Software except pursuant to a
Written License Agreement executed by the Licensor. Any use of the Software by
a Defense Practitioner without a valid Written License Agreement constitutes a
violation of this License and an infringement of the Licensor's copyright.

For purposes of clarity, the following uses by a Defense Practitioner are
expressly prohibited absent a Written License Agreement:

    (a) Use of the Software in any litigation, arbitration, mediation,
        administrative proceeding, or other dispute resolution process in which
        the Defense Practitioner represents an insurance company, manufacturer,
        governmental entity, common carrier, corporation, public utility, or
        other organization;

    (b) Integration of the Software into any product, service, platform, or tool
        used by or on behalf of any such organization;

    (c) Use of the Software for internal operations, training, research, or
        development by any such organization or by any law firm or attorney
        acting on behalf of such organization; and

    (d) Distribution of the Software or any Derivative Work to any other Defense
        Practitioner.


5. CHANGE IN STATUS

If a Consumer Attorney ceases to meet the definition of Consumer Attorney as set
forth in Section 1 (for example, by undertaking the ongoing defense of an
insurance company, manufacturer, governmental entity, common carrier,
corporation, public utility, or other organization in the types of litigation
described herein), the rights granted under Section 2 shall automatically
terminate, and such person or entity shall be classified as a Defense
Practitioner for purposes of this License. Such person or entity must either
(a) cease all use of the Software, or (b) obtain a Written License Agreement
from the Licensor within sixty (60) days of such change in status.

Conversely, if a Defense Practitioner comes to meet the definition of Consumer
Attorney, the rights under Section 2 shall automatically vest upon satisfaction
of the Consumer Attorney definition, provided that the person or entity notifies
the Licensor in writing of such change in status within thirty (30) days.


